{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab this script should ultimately help you to get rid of any MIDI Editor zooming issues. Assign it to the enter key and it will open\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab the MIDI Editor and zoom to 5 measures (default). Whereas the edit cursor represents the zoom center.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab You can adjust the measures in the user area.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The code is based to 99% on Julian's code, I only added the open MIDI editor command and cleaned up unnecessary parts.\sa180\par}
}

